{
  "local_port": 34142,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "PAN Card: I lost my Aadhaar card. How can I get a second copy?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you've lost your Aadhaar card. Fortunately, obtaining a duplicate Aadhaar card is a straightforward process. Below are several methods you can use to get a second copy of your Aadhaar card:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Online via the Official UIDAI Website**\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Visit the UIDAI Portal:**\n   - Go to the [UIDAI official website](https://uidai.gov.in/).\n\n2. **Navigate to \"My Aadhaar\":**\n   - On the homepage, hover over the **\"My Aadhaar\"** section in the top menu.\n\n3. **Select \"Download Aadhaar\":**\n   - Click on **\"Download Aadhaar\"** from the dropdown.\n\n4. **Choose Retrieval Method:**\n   - If you know your **Aadhaar Number (UID)**, select that option.\n   - If you don't know your Aadhaar Number but have your **Enrollment ID (EID)**, select the EID option.\n\n5. **Enter Required Details:**\n   - **Aadhaar Number Method:**\n     - Enter your 12-digit Aadhaar Number.\n     - Enter the registered mobile number.\n   - **Enrollment ID Method:**\n     - Enter your 28-digit Enrollment ID (EID) found on your acknowledgment letter.\n     - Enter the registered mobile number.\n\n6. **Verify via OTP:**\n   - An OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number. Enter the OTP to proceed.\n\n7. **Download Aadhaar:**\n   - Once verified, your Aadhaar card will be displayed on the screen. Click on **\"Download Aadhaar\"** to save the PDF copy.\n\n**Note:** Ensure that your mobile number is updated and registered with UIDAI to receive the OTP.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Using the mAadhaar Mobile App**\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Download the App:**\n   - Install the [**mAadhaar**](https://uidai.gov.in/en/get-your-aadhaar-uidai/download-aadhaar.html) app from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n\n2. **Launch the App:**\n   - Open the app and select **\"Download Aadhaar\"**.\n\n3. **Enter Details:**\n   - Provide either your **Aadhaar Number (UID)** or **Enrollment ID (EID)** along with the registered mobile number.\n\n4. **Authenticate:**\n   - An OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number. Enter the OTP to verify.\n\n5. **Download Aadhaar:**\n   - After successful verification, you can download the Aadhaar PDF. You may be prompted to create a password to secure the PDF.\n\n**Advantages:**\n- Convenient and quick access on your mobile device.\n- Option to set a password for added security.\n\n---\n\n### **3. SMS Method (Retrieve Aadhaar Number)**\n\nIf you've forgotten your Aadhaar Number but know the registered mobile number, you can retrieve it via SMS.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Compose an SMS:**\n   - Type: `GET UID <12-digit mobile number>`\n   - Example: `GET UID 9876543210`\n\n2. **Send SMS:**\n   - Send the SMS to **5676789** from your registered mobile number.\n\n3. **Receive Aadhaar Number:**\n   - You will receive an SMS with the last four digits of your Aadhaar Number.\n\n**Note:** Once you have your Aadhaar Number, you can use the [online method](#1-online-via-the-official-uidai-website) to download your Aadhaar card.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Visit an Aadhaar Enrollment Center**\n\nIf online methods are not feasible, you can visit the nearest Aadhaar Enrollment Center to apply for a duplicate Aadhaar card.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Locate the Nearest Center:**\n   - Use the [UIDAI Enrollment Center Locator](https://appointment.uidai.gov.in/) to find the nearest center.\n\n2. **Gather Required Documents:**\n   - **Proof of Identity (POI):** e.g., PAN Card, Passport, Voter ID, etc.\n   - **Proof of Address (POA):** e.g., Utility bill, bank statement, etc.\n   - **Proof of Date of Birth (DOB):** e.g., Birth certificate, SSLC certificate, etc.\n\n3. **Visit the Center:**\n   - Carry the required documents and fill out the Aadhaar correction form requesting a duplicate copy.\n\n4. **Biometric Authentication:**\n   - Your biometric details (fingerprints, iris scan) will be verified to authenticate your identity.\n\n5. **Receive Aadhaar Card:**\n   - After verification, your duplicate Aadhaar card will be sent to your registered address via post within 90 days.\n\n**Note:** It may take a few weeks to receive the duplicate Aadhaar card through this method.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Tips:**\n\n- **Keep Your Details Updated:** Ensure that your mobile number and address are up-to-date in the Aadhaar database to facilitate easy retrieval and delivery.\n  \n- **Secure Your Aadhaar Information:** Once you receive your duplicate copy, store it in a safe place to prevent loss or unauthorized access.\n  \n- **Avoid Third-Party Services:** Always use official UIDAI channels to avoid potential scams or misuse of your personal information.\n\n---\n\nFor more detailed information or assistance, you can visit the [**UIDAI Official Website**](https://uidai.gov.in/) or contact UIDAI customer support:\n\n**UIDAI Contact Details:**\n- **Helpline Number:** 1947\n- **Email:** help@uidai.gov.in\n\nStay safe and ensure to keep a digital or physical copy of your Aadhaar card in a secure location to avoid future inconveniences.",
